record.notes:
Lang, Adrianne. 1973. Enga dictionary with English index. Canberra: Pacific Linguistics.
Enga is the most widely spoken Trans-New Guinea language. Dialects include Laiapo, Mai, Lyaime, Papayuku, and Torenama.
